  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Peel and grate the <strong>potatoes</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>grated potato</strong> to the middle of a tea towel and bring the four corners together to form a ball, twist the ball and squeeze out as much of the liquid as you can</p>\n<p>Add the squeezed <strong>potato</strong> to a bowl with 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tsp]</span> of <strong>salt</strong> and a pinch of<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a sheet of <strong>non-stick</strong> <strong>baking paper</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) and drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>grated potato </strong>to one side of the baking paper and shape into a rectangle (press it down hard to make it as thin as possible!)</p>\n<p>Drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden brown and crispy – this is your <strong>potato rosti</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the potato rosti is cooking, peel and finely dice the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></span></p>\n<p>Strip the <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</span></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>thyme </strong>and <strong>garlic</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rosti has had 10-12 min, add the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the other side of the tray</p>\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, drizzle with <strong>olive oil </strong>and return the tray to the oven for 10-12 min further or until the broccoli is golden and tender and the rosti is cooked through</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2406Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>cherry tomatoes </strong>in half</p>\n<p>Drain and rinse the <strong>butter beans </strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>tomato paste</strong> to the softened onion and cook for 1 min further</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> with the <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>and reduce the heat to low</p>\n<p>Cook, covered, for 5-6 min further or until the tomatoes have broken down to create a sauce</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
